Save tabs and tab groups. Restore them later.

Tab IQ can save or restore entire windows with ease. Click to save the current tabs. For fun, don’t forget to add tab groups, colors, and more. Later, click on the time that it was saved to open a fresh window with that state. No need to save tabs to disk. All of the tabs can stay in the browser. That way they’ll be much easier to find later.

The current maximum number of windows saved is 100. That number can be changed with a feature request, if there’s good justification. Newly available features now include the ability to rename windows in the listing or to even possibly add icons and images. Enjoy.
